<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Spring Rolls</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>8-10 spring roll wrappers</li>
            <li>2 cups cooked and shredded chicken or shrimp (or tofu for a vegetarian option)</li>
            <li>1 cup vermicelli noodles, cooked and cooled</li>
            <li>1 cup shredded lettuce</li>
            <li>1 cup matchstick-cut carrots</li>
            <li>1/2 cup bean sprouts</li>
            <li>Fresh mint leaves and cilantro for flavor</li>
            <li>Dipping sauce (hoisin sauce, peanut sauce, or sweet chili sauce)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Appetizer</li>
            <li>Asian</li>
            <li>Healthy</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Prepare all the filling ingredients: cooked and shredded chicken or shrimp, vermicelli noodles, shredded lettuce, matchstick-cut carrots, bean sprouts, mint leaves, and cilantro.</li>
            <li>Fill a shallow dish with warm water. Dip one spring roll wrapper into the water for about 5 seconds until it softens.</li>
            <li>Place the softened wrapper on a clean surface. Add a small amount of each filling ingredient to the center of the wrapper.</li>
            <li>Roll up the wrapper, folding in the sides, to form a tight spring roll. Repeat with the remaining wrappers and filling ingredients.</li>
            <li>Serve the spring rolls with your choice of dipping sauce.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Spring Rolls!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

